{"key":"processedPost-8559232","value":{"id":8559232,"first":8558935,"last":8559247,"when":1214349903,"utime":"06/25/08 02:25 AM","content":"You want to fill your jars loosely, but make sure there's no air pockets created as you load.&nbsp; If you're not careful, a 'clump' might cause the area around and under it not to fill, and then it comes apart and settles during sterilization.&nbsp; Don't pack, but it doesn't hurt to slap the side of the jar a time or two as you fill, and especially after topping with dry verm.&nbsp; Tap the side of the jar with a wooden spoon or something, and then replace any verm that settles.&nbsp; If using upside down lids, you can actually fill the verm a little bit above the edge of the jar and it fits into the divot on the lid.<br />At this point, since your verm barrier might have slipped down the sides, I'd suggest covering the 4 holes with micropore medical tape, and then sticking another piece right over the first one after you inoculate.<br />RR<br />","title":"Re: Shrunken Cakes After PC"}}